Polymorphism: Greek word. Multiple forms.

It is an ability of an object to take many forms

Two types of Polymorphism.
    Compile time Polymorphism
    Runtime Polymorphism


Compile time polymorphism is a type of polymorphism which can be achieved at Java compilation time.
Compile time polymorphism is also known as Static polymorphism or early binding.
Compile time polymorphism is achieved using Method Overloading.


Runtime Poly can be achieved at runtime or execution time
Also known as Dynamic poly or Dynamic method dispatch.
This can be achieved using Method Overriding concept